Disposition.DispositionRationale: The symptoms must be assessed, even if they have improved. It is best that they are seen by a local service to ensure continuity of care. Referral to out of hours service is not appropriate.

TriageLine.ReportText: Before you go, I will just check whether I need to give you any further instructions or advice.
Any thoughts about ending your life or harming yourself - CONTACT THE GP PRACTICE OR OUT OF HOURS SERVICE IMMEDIATELY.
You can also access support via nhs.uk (search for mental health support) or contact a healthcare professional.
If there are any new symptoms, or if the condition gets worse, changes or you have any other concerns, call us back.
Remember to take a list of any current medications if you go to the out of hours surgery.
